<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-07T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">741.9411/34: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-07T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                        1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 7—9:32
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>900. Your May 10, noon, and May 24, 7 p.m. The chance has been found to
                            convey informally your suggestions in substance to the Foreign Office. I
                            have been given assurance that they will be fully considered and that in
                            any redrafting of the Anglo–Japanese Treaty of Alliance it will be made
                            quite clear that the Alliance is not aimed at the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>